<h2>How AI Search Changes the SEO vs PPC Equation</h2>
<p><a href="/blog/optimize-google-ai-overviews/">AI Overviews</a> now appear on a growing percentage of Google searches. When an AI summary appears at the top of the results page, traditional organic CTR drops from 15% to 8%, according to <a href="https://outreachz.com/blog/seo-vs-ppc-in-2026/">OutreachZ</a>.</p>
<p>This creates a new dynamic for both channels.</p>
<h3>Impact on SEO</h3>
<p>AI Overviews cite sources. Sites that get cited in AI summaries see CTR jump from 0.6% to 1.08%. The goal shifts from ranking in position 1 to <a href="/blog/get-cited-ai-search/">getting cited by AI search engines</a>.</p>
<p>Optimizing for <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">Generative Engine Optimization</a> (GEO) requires structured content with clear answers, authoritative citations, and <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup</a>. These are the same signals that drive traditional SEO. GEO is an extension of SEO, not a replacement.</p>
<h3>Impact on PPC</h3>
<p>AI Overviews push paid ads further down the page on some queries. But Google protects its ad revenue. Shopping ads, Local Service Ads, and branded search ads continue to appear prominently.</p>
<p>PPC costs are rising. 87% of industries saw increased average CPCs in 2025, according to <a href="https://hallam.agency/blog/ppc-vs-seo-which-channel-delivers-the-best-roi-in-2026/">WordStream via Hallam</a>. As AI search reduces organic CTR on some queries, advertisers compete more aggressively for the remaining paid clicks.</p>
<h3>The Combined Strategy</h3>
<p>The businesses winning in 2026 run both channels with a clear division of labor:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>SEO</strong> handles informational queries, <a href="/blog/what-is-content-cluster/">content clusters</a>, long-tail keywords, and AI citation optimization</li>
<li><strong>PPC</strong> handles high-intent commercial queries, brand defense, retargeting, and quick-launch campaigns</li>
</ul>
<p>Neither channel alone captures the full search opportunity. Together, they cover the entire buyer journey from research to purchase.</p>
<h3>Using PPC Data to Improve SEO</h3>
<p>Run PPC campaigns on 20 to 30 target keywords for 2 to 4 weeks. Measure which keywords generate actual conversions, not just clicks. The keywords with the highest PPC conversion rates are the keywords worth building <a href="/blog/seo-content-writing/">SEO content</a> around.</p>
<p>This test-first approach saves months of wasted SEO effort. A keyword with 10,000 monthly searches and zero PPC conversions will likely deliver the same result organically: traffic without revenue. Validate demand with PPC before committing SEO resources.</p>
<p>PPC ad copy data also informs SEO. The headlines and descriptions with the highest CTR in ads become the basis for organic <a href="/glossary/title-tag/">title tags</a> and <a href="/blog/write-meta-descriptions/">meta descriptions</a> that earn more clicks from the SERP.</p>
